Knowledge base.
---------------

To search fast large area (binary?) one can use: https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/utility/functional/boyer_moore_searcher
 however, I have hit an issue when compiling on AIX

To access large file whithout need to allocate a buffer and copy by hand, one can use: 
https://www.ibm.com/docs/en/zos/3.1.0?topic=functions-mmap-map-pages-memory#mmap
resp. munmap to release

You can use sliceTape.pl to slice the EBCDIC encoded tape. This is pure perl, hence slower.
